text.tspan: People in rich countries often consume ten times more resources
than people in poor countries do, and so do their children
Some hope to conserve resources by having mothers bear
fewer children, often looking to places with high birth rates
Multiplyting birth rates and resources use gives another
perspective. Mothers in Luxembourg, Quatar, Israel
and Australia bring many times more resource use to
the world than mothers in Pakistan, India, or Africa
